body:
The module is at https://www.dropbox.com/s/r6x8bqdc4tldwop/model.pt?dl=0.  You should be able to reproduce the problem with simply

```c++
#include <torch/script.h>

int main() {
    torch::jit::load("model.pt");
    return 0;
}
```

On the other hand, writing `torch.jit.load("model.pt")` in Python does work.  So this may be some sort of inconsistency between the latest nightly builds of the Python and C++ libraries.
